The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 BJP fund for disaster

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, Dec. 28: The BJP today set up a calamity relief fund to help the tsunami-hit people while party chief L.K. Advani urged the Centre to declare the disaster a national calamity.

 Advani also said an insurance scheme ought to be set up to provide social security to those living near the sea.

 Former Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee announced the setting up of the relief fund after chairing a meeting of senior BJP leaders who took stock of the tsunami disaster.

 ?Lakhs of people have been affected by this devastating natural calamity in different parts of the country. They need urgent relief. The BJP has set up an apna rahat kosh and we appeal to all countrymen to contribute to it with an open mind,? Vajpayee said after the meeting. 




